    "The study of propagation of acoustic waves in a radiating fluid using Newton's cooling law predicts an adiabatic propagation for waves with periods significantly shorter than τ R, while in the opposite case acoustic waves propagate isothermally.",
    "However, at low enough frequencies the wavelength of the fluctuations becomes long enough so that the perturbation becomes optically thick, and the Newtonian cooling approximation is no longer valid.",
